This paper deals with the problem of learning schemas from examples in unordered XML, which is a topic related to databases (cs.DB) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The learning framework proposed in the paper is inspired by Gold's learning model, which is a well-known framework in computational learning theory (cs.LG). The paper also discusses the efficiency of the learning algorithms, which is a topic related to data structures (cs.DS) and computational linguistics (cs.CL).
